The paper deals with lower bounds and constructions for data structures, specifically two-bitprobe adaptive schemes storing five elements. This falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in the analysis of lower bounds. The use of probabilistic techniques and complexity theory suggests that it could also fall under the categories of computational complexity (cs.CC) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper involves combinatorics and graph theory in the analysis of lower bounds, which could place it under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
